reviews.review_text:
Listening Listeing to this version of my 1st show this early morning in March 2014. Wow, I just love this band so many years ago that I still come to this site and listen to at least 1 show EVERY DAY. Back in 1979 I did not know a lot about the band ( in fact really knew nothing compared to today ) yet for ever glad I was here. Within a year or two I was full steam ahead and loving every minute of the music. 
 Another Great copy of that faithful day. To the taper you made some very AWESOME quality tapes you knew the spot to capture our love. And very glad you share it with us all.  1000 THANK YOU'S 
 Gets 5 stars because sound is good but more so because was the day that changed my life.

bread crumb Listening to this run of shows for which only audience tapes are available has been a real pleasure.  The quality of recordings are all in the range that would have happily made my pre-IA collection.  More importantly it reminded me, after listening to an awful lot of sound boards, how happy we were just to be there, regardless of the set list, the quality of the playing or any of the other common criticisms one sees in these commentaries.  We are well and truly spoiled.
